\fs32 \cf2 You've put your finger on the single most important branding question for Humanity.llc.\
The risk is real. If someone scans a QR code on a purse and lands on a freelancer profile, they might think: "Oh, this is for freelancers. I'm not a freelancer. Next."\
You lose them forever.\
But you can solve this by designing the scan experience to be two things at once: a verification of that person and an invitation to this movement.\
Let me think this through carefully.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs44 \cf2 \cb1 The Core Insight: Every Profile Is A Recruitment Tool\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 The person scanning the QR code is not your customer yet. They are a curious stranger. Your job is not to sell them freelance services. Your job is to make them ask: "How do I get one of those QR codes?"\
That means the profile page cannot be just a resume. It must be a portal into the movement.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
